<p><br />
The group is based at Polytechnique Montréal, one of Canada’s top engineering research universities and led by <a href="https://www.polymtl.ca/phys/en/stephane-kena-cohen">Prof. Stéphane Kéna-Cohen</a>.</p>

<p><strong>We are always looking for passionate new PhD students, Postdocs, and Master students to join the team.</strong> <a href="http://localhost:4000/vacancies">(more info)</a> <strong>!</strong> Prospective students: For many years now, Montréal has been <a href="https://www.topuniversities.com/student-info/university-news/montreal-named-worlds-best-student-city">ranked by QS as the World’s best student city</a>.</p>

<p>We are members of two indersciplinary strategic groups in Québec, <a href="https://www.rqmp.ca">the Regroupement Québécois sur les Matériaux de Pointe (RQMP)</a> and the <a href="https://www.intriq.org">Institut Transdisciplinaire d’Information Quantique (INTRIQ)</a>.</p>
